cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with visual perception of numerosity and uses deep networks to simulate human performance. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the computational bases of numerosity perception and uses neural networks to model it. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible categories as the paper uses machine learning techniques to simulate human performance and discusses the role of specialized systems in numerical representation. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the developmental changes in numerosity perception and the impact of non-numerical features, which are relevant to human-computer interaction.
